## Step 4 ŌĆö Manual zip + release (fallback)

If Actions is down, disabled, or you cannot wait for CI.

### 4a ŌĆö Zip with .NET `ZipFile` (forward slashes only)

Use **.NET `System.IO.Compression.ZipFile`**, not **`Compress-Archive`**, so entry names use **`/`** (Linux-safe).

Exclude **`.git`**, **`.github`**, and **`.cursor`** so the package matches CI and does not ship dev metadata.

```powershell
$PluginRoot = (Get-Location).Path
$zipPath    = Join-Path (Split-Path $PluginRoot -Parent) "hostlinks-marketing-ops.zip"

if (Test-Path $zipPath) { Remove-Item $zipPath -Force }

Add-Type -AssemblyName System.IO.Compression.FileSystem
$zip = [System.IO.Compression.ZipFile]::Open($zipPath, 'Create')

Get-ChildItem -Path $PluginRoot -Recurse -File | Where-Object {
    $p = $_.FullName
    $p -notmatch '[\\/]\.git[\\/]' -and
    $p -notmatch '[\\/]\.github[\\/]' -and
    $p -notmatch '[\\/]\.cursor[\\/]'
} | ForEach-Object {
    $relative = $_.FullName.Substring($PluginRoot.Length + 1).Replace('\', '/')
    $entry    = "hostlinks-marketing-ops/$relative"
    [System.IO.Compression.ZipFileExtensions]::CreateEntryFromFile($zip, $_.FullName, $entry, 'Optimal') | Out-Null
}

$zip.Dispose()
```

### 4b ŌĆö GitHub CLI

```powershell
Set-Location $PluginRoot
gh release create 1.X.X $zipPath --title "v1.X.X - Short title" --notes "Changelog here."
# or replace asset only:
gh release upload 1.X.X $zipPath --clobber
```

